(not 3,6-dimethylcyclohexane)

I -ethyl-3-methylcyclopentane
(not I-methyl-4-ethylcyclopentane)

The substituent groups derived from cycloalkanes by removing one hydrogen are named by replacing the ending -ane of the hydrocarbon with -yl to
give cycloalkyl. Thus cyclohexane becomes cyclohexyl; cyclopentane,
cyclopentyl; and so on.

