H. P O L Y M E R I Z A T I O N O F A L K E N E S

One of the most important industrial reactions of alkenes is their conversion
to higher-molecular-weight compounds (polymers). A polymer is here defined as a long-chain molecule with recurring structural units. Polymerization
of propene, for example, gives a long-chain hydrocarbon with recurring
units. Most industrially important polymerizations of alkenes
