In water solution most aldehydes form hydrates. This reaction is analogous

to hemiacetal formation and is catalyzed by both acids and bases. The equilibrium constant for hydrate formation depends on steric and electrical factors.
In contrast to hemiacetal formation, acetal formation is catalyzed only by
