12.4 ketenes
Substances with cumulated carbonyl and carbon-carbon double bonds,
\
C = C = O , are called ketenes and, as might be expected, have interesting
/
and unusual properties.
There are few general preparations for ketenes although several special
methods are available for ketene itself. The most convenient laboratory preparation is to pass acetone vapor over a coil of resistance wire heated electrically to a dull red heat. Air is excluded to avoid simple combustion.
