catalyzed by acids, since addition of a proton or formation of a hydrogen
bond to the carbonyl oxygen makes the carbonyl carbon more strongly
electropositive and hence more vulnerable to nucleophilic attack. The following equations illustrate an acid-catalyzed reaction involving a negatively
