equally well as 2-hydroxyethylamine or as 2-aminoethanol, although by eonvention 2-aminoethanol is favored, since hydroxyl normally takes precedence
over amino. With halogens the situation is reversed, and 2-chloroethylamine
is favored over Zaminoethyl chloride. Some typical amines with the names
which they have in common use are listed in Table 16.2 together with their
physical properties.
