Many of the.drugs that have been used in cancer therapy are chloroalkylamines whose effectiveness appears to be associated with their alkylating
ability. The so-called nitrogen mustards [2], containing two chloroethyl
groups, react by a sequence of displacement steps. The chlorine is displaced

