As a rnethylating agent for moderately acidic substances, diazomethane
has nearly ideal properties. It can be used in organic solvents; it reacts very
rapidly without need for a catalyst; the coproduct is nitrogen, which offers
no separation problem; it gives essentially quantitative yields; and, because
of its color and the appearance of bubbles of nitrogen, it acts as its own indicator to show when reaction is complete. With acids it gives esters and with
enols it gives 0-alkylation.

