summary
Organic nitrogen compounds include amines (RNH,), amine salts
(RNH3@xe),amides (RCONH,), nitriles (RCsN), isocyanates (RNCO),

summary

445

hydrazlnes (RNHNHR), azo compounds (RN=NR), diazo compounds
(RCHN,), azides (RN,), nitroso compounds (RNO), and nitro compounds
(RN02).
Amines are associated by hydrogen bonding to a moderate extent and as a
result they are more volatile than hydrocarbons but less volatile than alcohols of the same molecular weight. However, amines are more soluble in
water than alcohols because they form strong hydrogen bonds with the
protons of hydroxylic compounds. Amines, like ammonia, undergo rapid
and are
inversion at nitrogen. Aliphatic amines are weak bases (KB
very'feeble acids (KHA lo-,,).
