Rearrangement of phenyl allyl-3-14C ether at 200" gives o-allyl-l-l4Cphenol. What does this tell you about the rearrangement mechanism? Can
it be a dissociation-recombination process'? What product(s) would you expect from a para Claisen rearrangement of 2,6-dimethylphenyl allyl-3-14C
