Steric and electronic effects are important in stabilizing these three entities. All absorb light in the visible region of the spectrum. Radicals, in addition, can be detected and identified by epr spectroscopy.
The reactions of meta- and para-substituted aromatic systems obey linear
free-energy relationships, one of which is the Hammett equation, log k =
po + log k,. This expresses a rate constant for the reaction of a meta- or
para-substituted aryl compound in terms of k, (the rate constant for the
rate of the unsubstituted compound), p (the reaction constant, which is
independent of the substituent), and o (the substituent constant, which is
independent of the reaction). A similar relationship holds for equilibrium
constants.

