Among the natural products related to pyridine, we have already mentioned
the coenzyme nicotinamide-adenine dinucleotide (NADO, Figure 18.3). Other
important pyridine derivatives include nicotine, nicotinic acid (niacin, antipellagra factor), and pyridoxine (vitamin B,). Coniine is a toxic alkaloid
which occurs in the shrub poison hemlock; it has a reduced pyridine (piperidine) ring.

