y-butyrolactam

Indeed, these reactions occur much more readily than their intermolecular
counterparts; y- and 6-hydroxyacids cyclize spontaneously to give lactones.
The same pattern applies to anhydride formation; heating acetic acid has
little effect but warming succinic acid or phthalic acid produces the anhydrides.

