isopentenyl pyrophosphate (IPP)

The formation of C,, compounds occurs by the condensation of one
molecule of IPP with one molecule of its structural isomer, 3,3-dimethylally1 pyrophosphate (3,3-D). This reaction involves a displacement of pyrophosphate from 3,3-D by the methylene carbon of IPP and the loss of a proton
from the C-2 position. The compound thus formed is a pyrophosphate
derivative of geraniol and is the precursor of the whole set of monoterpenes.

